<p>Canada is mourning after a deadly shooting in the remote British Columbia community of Tumbler Ridge left eight people dead. The suspected shooter also died, according to multiple reports. Authorities say the violence started at a private home and then moved to Tumbler Ridge Secondary School, rattling a small town where residents say nearly everyone knows someone affected. Police have identified the suspect as 18-year-old Jesse Van Rootselaar and say they are still working to determine a motive. On Feb. 13, Prime Minister Mark Carney plans to travel to Tumbler Ridge to meet residents and attend a vigil as the country grieves.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/RmzUG_VBdjOZ6jIxyVGY2gzoSoNj9tTJbU-6oMSwV3tFzWWCZIqLA4L-PHqNZp1g9ZnZ21MebmDApW_4S-Vcajw7v2fD3R4LiK_JPt3JBKoOrx8sgTuLnLmyWnyGiRUx3PLwOT_3HTIMtCSFcQHR2w8eN-x6cpNNC5BuI91E-0sbjRK_QVRdoVk_hfwXgPOMx5U6KWx74qypA8E3iprU9Cx8I6I' alt='Tumbler Ridge Secondary School on Wednesday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Victims remembered: Reports said the dead ranged in age from 11 to 39 and described several victims as children and a school staff member. Families and classmates have been sharing memories while planning vigils.</li><li>Families sought information: One account described relatives scrambling for answers in the hours after the attack, capturing the confusion and fear during the initial response.</li><li>Firearms previously seized and returned: Reporting citing officials said police seized firearms from the suspect’s home about two years ago but later returned them, raising questions about earlier intervention.</li><li>Questions on firearms: Police said the suspect’s firearms licence expired about two years ago, and reporting noted it remains unclear who owned the guns used in the attack.</li><li>Online activity: The New York Times reported the suspect’s online posts referenced mental health problems, substance abuse, and an interest in weapons and online violence, including violent extremism content.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Prime Minister Mark Carney: Carney plans to travel to Tumbler Ridge on Feb. 13 to meet mourners and attend a vigil. He has also invited leaders from all political parties to join him, according to reports. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/13/tumbler-ridge-shooting-victims-remembered-canada'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Local residents: Residents described a tight-knit town where nearly everyone knows someone affected. Coverage also highlighted neighbors rallying around grieving families and students. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/czj17z7l9jmo'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>Police and investigators: Authorities said they have not established a motive. They also described repeated prior police responses tied to concerns about the suspect’s mental health and weapons, as investigators continue to piece together what happened. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/12/police-visited-home-of-tumbler-ridge-suspect-multiple-times-over-mental-health-concerns'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Socialist Equality Party (WSWS): An opinion piece argued the shooting reflects broader &quot;social and political life in Canada&quot; and criticized political leaders and corporate media responses. (<a href='https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2026/02/13/sndf-f13.html'>World Socialist Web Site</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3343387/tumbler-ridge-grieves-8-killed-canadas-deadliest-shooting-years'>Tumbler Ridge grieves for 8 killed in Canada’s deadliest shooting in years</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/remote-canadian-community-grapples-with-aftermath-of-mass-shooting-that-left-9-people-dead'>Remote community grieves 8 killed in Canada&#x27;s deadliest attack in years</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/remote-canadian-community-grapples-aftermath-mass-shooting-left-130101978'>Remote Canadian community grapples with aftermath of mass shooting that left 9 people dead</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/carney-plans-visit-to-tumbler-ridge-on-friday-as-canada-grieves-mass-shooting'>Carney plans visit to Tumbler Ridge on Feb 13 as Canada grieves mass shooting</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/12/world/canada/tumbler-ridge-shooting-victims-canada.html'>What We Know About the Victims of the Tumbler Ridge Mass Shooting in Canada</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/12/canadas-pm-carney-to-visit-tumbler-ridge-after-mass-school-shooting'>Canada’s PM Carney to visit Tumbler Ridge after mass school shooting</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/13/tumbler-ridge-shooting-victims-remembered-canada'>‘The tears just keep flowing’: child victims of Tumbler Ridge shooting remembered as Carney heads to join vigil</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2026/02/13/sndf-f13.html'>The Tumbler Ridge mass shooting: An indictment of social and political life in Canada</a> - wsws.org</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/czj17z7l9jmo'>&#x27;Everyone knows somebody affected&#x27; - small Canadian town united in grief after mass shooting</a> - bbc.com</li></ul>